  "prompt": "What is the best all round fighter jet as of 2015?",
  "response": "As of 2015, the F-35 Lightning II was widely considered one of the best all-around fighter jets. Developed by Lockheed Martin, the F-35 is a fifth-generation multirole stealth fighter that combines advanced avionics, stealth capabilities, and versatility for various missions, including air-to-air combat, air-to-ground strikes, and intelligence, surveillance, and reconnaissance (ISR) tasks. Its ability to operate in various environments and its cutting-edge technology made it a standout choice among modern fighter aircraft at that time.\n\nOther notable fighter jets from that period include the F-22 Raptor, which is renowned for its air superiority and stealth features, as well as the Eurofighter Typhoon and the Dassault Rafale, both of which are also capable all-around multirole fighters. However, the F-35 gained significant attention due to its advanced features and the breadth of its intended roles across multiple platforms and nations.",
